SIMPLE: contemplative
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contemplative
<hw>Con*tem"pla*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>contemplatif</ets>, L. <ets>contemplativus</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to contemplation; addicted to, or employed
in, contemplation; meditative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fixed and <qex>contemplative</qex> their looks.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the power of contemplation; <as>as,
<ex>contemplative</ex> faculties</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contemplative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Contemplative
<hw>Con*tem"pla*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A
religious or either sex devoted to prayer and meditation, rather than to
active works of charity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contemplatively</ent>⟦br⟧
